com.foreach.across.modules.dynamicforms.domain.document.data

Class DynamicDocumentDataBinder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.foreach.across.modules.dynamicforms.domain.document.data.DynamicDocumentDataBinder

  • public final class DynamicDocumentDataBinder
extends Object
    Special purpose object for use with a DataBinder. Contains a single property getFields() which provides Map access to the underlying document.

    When using a DynamicDocumentDataBinder instance as a child property or a bean that is the actual target of the databinder, it is imperative that the correct pathPrefix is set, to ensure that conversion exceptions are caught by the binder and converted into a typeMismatch error.

    Let's say you have a target bean with a document property that is the DynamicDocumentDataBinder. Then the configured prefix should also be document, with property paths being document.fields[my.key].

    This instance usually expects a ConversionService that should be used when converting input values to the target type. If a null value is passed for the ConversionService, no type conversion will be done.

    Since:
    0.0.1
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
